## 1. Binary representation


**Problem 1.1** What is the binary representation of $1/5$?   

**SOLUTION**  
Hence we  show that
$$
\begin{aligned}
(0.00110011001100â€¦)_2 &= (2^{-3} + 2^{-4})(1.00010001000â€¦)_2 =  (2^{-3} + 2^{-4}) \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} {1 \over 16^k} \\
&= {2^{-3} + 2^{-4} \over 1 - {1\over 2^4}} = \frac{1}{5}
\end{aligned}
$$

